Since the primed lemma linter has dropped (I think), can you add a docstring explaining how this lemma is distinct from `identical_iff`?
These should go higher up on the file, right after the definitions of `memâ‚—` and `memáµ£`. You can also remove the blank line between them, since they're very simple related lemmas.

Is this not just
```suggestion
/-- If `x` and `y` are identical, then a left move of `y` is identical to some left move of `x`. -/
lemma Identical.moveLeft_symm : âˆ€ {x y}, x â‰¡ y â†’
    âˆ€ i, âˆƒ j, x.moveLeft j â‰¡ y.moveLeft i  := fun hxy â†¦ hxy.symm.moveLeft
```
Given this information, do you really think we need this?
They are not identical. It needs to be written as `fun hxy i â†¦ (hxy.symm.moveLeft i).imp fun _ â†¦ .symm`. But this lemma probably does not really matter.
